Incorporation of linuxcnc-features into LinuxCNC git tree

Constituents in the LinuxCNC git tree:
  1) share/features ----------------------- all non-program components 
  2) lib/python/gladevcp/features.py ------ 'the main program'
  3) configs/sim/axis/features_demo/ ------ axis gui demos
     configs/sim/gmoccapy/features_demo/ -- gmoccapy gui demos
  4) bin/features ------------------------- copied (by make) from features.py   


Notes:
  1) deb install or Run-In-Place (RIP) build
     for axis gui, use [DISPLAY]GLADEVCP=  (see demos)
     for gmoccapy gui, use EMBED_TAB_*=    (see demos)

  2) Standalone usage:
     $ features --help
     Standalone Usage:
        features [Options]
     Options:
        -h | --help
        -i inifilename | --ini=inifilename
     Notes:
       1) for standalone usage:
             a) specify an inifile name which specifies [DISPLAY]FEATURES_PATH
          or
             b) start in a working directory with appropriate subdirs (catalogs etc)
       2) default catalog is: lathe
       3) Program location: /usr/bin/features

  3) translation support files located in:
       share/features/locale
     are present but not incorporated

  4) When a config is started without a catalogs/type/menu.xml file, the appropriate
     system SYS_PATH/catalogs/type/menu.xml file is copied to the configuration's
     [DISPLAY]FEATURES_PATH/catalogs/type/menu.xml

     Similarly, a missing catalogs/type/defaultgs.ngc file is copied
     from the SYS_PATH.
   

